{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create a legal right for families to request copies of CCTV of homicide victims ",
        "additional_details": "Families of homicide victims are sometimes permitted to view CCTV of their loved ones, but police can refuse to provide copies for families to keep, claiming the footage belongs to a third party. Our strong view it that viewing footage in a controlled police room is not enough. Families can feel trapped by red tape and denied the right to retain these final records. We demand a legal framework compelling police to provide families with copies of this CCTV, bypassing third-party ownership and copyright reasons.",
        "background": "We want to create a statutory right for families of homicide victims to obtain physical/digital copies of CCTV footage featuring their deceased loved one. This should be known as James\u2019s Law,  so Police aren\u2019t stopped from providing copies to families by citing third-party ownership/data protection.",
